Well, I think it was poor conduct on behalf of the Elven Blades leadership to take an action that irrevocably removed them from The Fellowship (an alliance of guilds) before informing the fellowship of their decision.  Yes it was only a matter of hours, that still bothers me.<br>
<br>
Kolani, you can set up a dichotomy between lore and mechanics if you like.   I'm not going to accept it exists because I accept that in a role-playing <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>game</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> as opposed to freeform RP just because something exists in game lore does not mean it is open to players to play.  You can't play a Dragon in AD&amp;D for example.<br>
<br>
Tuppen,<br>
<br>
there's one more point that has to be added to your observations.<br>
<br>
If everyone wants to ignore the restrictions placed on them by the <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>creators</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> of the game (nobody seems to acknowledge their creativity while they are defending their own creative rights) then RP among people with highly disparate world views is going to be difficult, if not impossible.  That's why I can't RP on FV anymore.  Whenever I try I wind up spending all my time debating what I thought were supposed to be givens about how the world works and can't actually get to any RP.<br>
