<br>
Because I came from Mushes first, perhaps my mentality is the Mush mentality (Or moo as you call it. Whatever <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> , I hate MOO's <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ). I refuse to roleplay my character is a racist, bigoted wood elf, despite what game lore or mechanics might dictate.<br>
<br>
You don't have to like that, you don't have to RP with me. RP with the people in your cicle who think as you do, and I will RP with the people who do not mind my outlook and who are more flexible.<br>
<br>
This game is more than big enough where I don't dictate at you, and you don't dictate at me. *shrug*<br>
<br>
Same mostly goes on Mushes btw. There are some 'rules' of cannon, but for the most part people are allowed to RP as they see fit as long as it isn't too extremely against the dictates of the canon set down. As far as I know very very few people violate that here on EQ. *shrug*<br>
<br>
The only biggest pet peeve I have with EQ folks is their tendancy to power-play. And by that, I mean forcing an action on another player without that player's consent while rping. Please folks don't say you smacked me down unless I decide I want my character smacked down. *shrug* And more often than not, I'm going to be cool with my character getting smacked down if I think its appropriate.<br>
<br>
<br>
So you go ahead and be stereotypical and follow the game mechanics while I do my own style of free form. And we'll all be happy. <br>
End of story. Folks, do what you want as long as you're not hurting someone else. Keep in mind that you don't have to interact with anyone that you do not want to interact with.<br>
