You spend sooooooooo much time here telling everyone how they are playing wrong, and then you say you cant/dont roleplay yourself.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Nope.  I have never said people play wrong.  I have consistently said that lacking a common worldview among players leads to incompatable RP and, consistent with that, incompatible RP forced me to stop RPing.<br>
<br>
My background in RP is from LARPs, usually organizing them.  As a LARP organizier I expect everyone RPing to be creating one large, cohesive story.  I came started playing Firiona Vie (and, by necessity) EverQuest because I was led to believe that was going to be the case here.  I feel it generally was before the infamous May 8th patch.  I no longer feel it is.  As a result I stopped role-playing on FV because it fails to meet <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>my</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> needs in a role-playing game.  I found other ways to enjoy myself playing, and found myself with a lot of free time, so I am currently playing.<br>
<br>
Everyone else can play how they want.  But understand that the lack of a common worldview leads, more and more, to people forced to RP only in small circles.  <br>
<br>
I <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>do not</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> blame the players.  I blame Sony for not making any effort to establish and maintain a game environment conducive to large scale RP in what is advertised and sold as a role-playing game.<br>
<br>
Ideally there should be about 8 RP servers.  One with fixed alignments, one with a compeltely free will based alignment system, even one where any race can worship any god.  But that's not going to happen because Sony has no commitment to RP. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=irexes>Irexes</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Scythe matters<br>
