<br>
An FV where everyone agreed on the way things should be done would be very bland.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Every</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> good character grouping with evils &lt;&lt;---- bland<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>Every</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> good character not grouping with evils &lt;&lt;--- bland<br>
<br>
Some of each &lt;&lt;----- a tension which has a ring of authenticity about it<br>
<br>
Now to resort to analogies (which is a fatuous way to make a point, but meh).<br>
<br>
I live in the real world.<br>
In the real world some people believe in god and join religions.<br>
I think that religions are nonsense (all of them, even yours) and the notion of god is just plain daft.<br>
However I am able to exist in a world where for some people the reality of god is an established fact (albeit based on faith).<br>
And the universe continues to operate.<br>
I look at them and think.  Hah hah look at the unenlightened fools.<br>
They look at me and think. Hah hah look at the unenlightened fool.<br>
And from our own world views <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>we are both right</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.<br>
<br>
By the same token I see no problem with the Elf beastlord being simultaneously an Elf beastlord who looks like a Troll and a Troll who thinks he's an Elf beastlord depending on who you are.  In fact it can be happily incorporated into roleplay that would keep both sides happy (there's nothing more fun than a debate with a god-botherer for me and I'm sure they feel the same).<br>
<br>
Unfortunately I don't think this is the reason for the ire which these debates generate.  More to do with the tribe instinct in all of us and the desire to belong to a group with which you identify.  And there's no point being in a group if it's open to everyone.<br>
<br>
So argue on people, cause from this lizard's perspective everyone's right.  Especially me. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.irexes.pwp.blueyonder.co.uk/incitatus/index.html"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.irexes.pwp.blueyonder.co.uk/incitatus/pics/suspect.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><br>
