<br>
Kolani, it is true that I agree with the comments put forth by Loganhex more than those put forth by Kreelos.  It seems that my point is being missed because folks are getting hung up small points that Kreelos made.<br>
<br>
My point isn't game mechanics vs. RP.  My point is that people should roleplay how they want to roleplay, but should not and cannot dictate how my character will react to their character.  <br>
<br>
My character firmly believes that characters outside the norm are deceptive buggers and should be treated just like the rest of the characters of their race/class unless a consistent personal history of interaction proves otherwise (and that interaction just isn't going to happen in my character's case, because he will never be open minded enough to let a relationhip get started).<br>
<br>
Everyone should roleplay how they choose.  I simply suggest that they don't tell me that I am roleplaying Tuppen wrong because he refuses to accept their backstory of a being a &quot;good teir dal or an &quot;elven beastlord&quot; regardless of the &quot;exceptions&quot; in the lore of Norrath.  If they try to tell me that I am wrong, then they are hypocrites.<br>
<br>
And as for not RPing because everyone doesn't follow the same ruleset.  Hogwash.  I just avoid people who might try to disrupt my roleplay, and Tuppen typically ignores arguments regarding what constitutes good and evil.  Just because someone wants to bring it up, doesn't mean I have to indulge them. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#A62A2A>- </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie>Firiona Vie</a><font color=#A62A2A> - </font><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm49>The Dead Horse Forum</a> <font color=#A62A2A> - </font><br><br><br><br>Powered By <a href=http://www.ezboard.com/>ezboard®</a> Ver. 7.31c<br>Copyright ©1999-2004 ezboard, Inc.</center></body></html>  